node.title: Texas to Host Football Game for 90,000 Fans Despite Austin's Cancelled Veterans Day Parade
node.description: There's a reason Austin can host some big events, and not others, during COVID protocols.

node.title: Lukashenko accused of 'inhuman, gangster-style approach' to migrants
node.description: The humanitarian crisis on the Belarusian border deepens as thousands wait while EU nations stiffen border patrols and accuse the Belarusian government of "gangster style" behaviour.

node.title: The world's biggest shopping event starts tomorrow. Here's what you need to know
node.description: Selling more goods than Black Friday and Cyber Monday combined, China's "anti-Valentine's Day" has transformed from a movement dedicated to singles' self-care into the world's largest 24-hour shopping spree.

node.title: Dean Stockwell from Quantum Leap, countless films, dies aged 85
node.description: Dean Stockwell was a top Hollywood child actor who gained new success in middle age with the sci-fi series Quantum Leap and a string of indelible film performances.

node.title: Queensland set for a drenching over the coming days
node.description: The Bureau of Meteorology forecasts widespread falls of 20 to 50 millimetres, but some areas of the state could see totals exceeding 100 millimetres.

node.title: Rainfall records expected to tumble in NSW as state braces for flooding
node.description: The Bureau of Meteorology is forecasting falls of more than 150 millimetres, with communities in the north-west of NSW and near the Queensland border expected to bear the brunt of heavy downpours.

node.title: One reason 2022 looks like an ideal time for a government to land re-election
node.description: All sorts of things determine election outcomes but the economy is one and right now it could scarcely look better for the government, writes Peter Martin.

node.title: Australia's climate policy dead last in latest Climate Change Performance Index
node.description: Australia ranked 55th overall but was dead last in climate policy, the only country to receive no score in that category.

node.title: Rescue underway of motorist trapped in rising floodwaters of Todd River
node.description: Northern Territory Emergency Services are attempting to rescue a man trapped by rising floodwaters after his car was swept off the Wills Terrace causeway in Alice Springs' Todd River.

node.title: ACT records nine cases of COVID-19, no hospitalisations for the first time since August
node.description: The ACT has recorded nine new cases of COVID-19 as, for the first time since early in Canberra's lockdown, there are no people in hospital with the virus.

node.title: Sam Kerr dominates as Chelsea rout Champions League rivals 7-0
node.description: Matildas captain Sam Kerr has a hand in four of Chelsea's seven goals as they ease past Swiss side Servette in Champions League action overnight.

node.title: 'This country has gone mad': Brisbane cafe owner says he won't 'discriminate' against unvaccinated customers
node.description: Phillip Di Bella said his stance was about not vaccination status, but entirely based on his concern that human rights were being degraded by upcoming public health order.

node.title: Tom Hanks, a real-life rescue dog and a robot sidekick team up in post-apocalyptic buddy comedy
node.description: It’s a hard heart that can resist the Hollywood star's latest adventure, in which he plays a robotics engineer on a road trip through a dystopian landscape - in good company.

node.title: Private 'catch-and-release' quarantine scheme could soon be up and running for non-Australians
node.description: A company established by an influential Liberal party figure says it could bring up to 160,000 foreign workers and students a year into Australia via a private hotel quarantine system with support from the Home Affairs Department.

node.title: Thousands skip Northern Territory quarantine without paying
node.description: The Northern Territory government is chasing an estimated $6.3 million from travellers who have not paid for their stay in mandatory quarantine.

node.title: Carole Baskin suing Netflix over her Tiger King 2 interviews
node.description: While Florida big cat sanctuary founder Carole Baskin has launched legal action over use of her interviews in Tiger King 2, Netflix says she and her husband agreed in writing that the material could be used in future and that she is trying to block the company's right to free speech.

node.title: Concerns for Adelaide's Port River dolphins after foam cleaning balls found on shore
node.description: An investigation is underway into how foam cleaning balls from a nearby power station were found on the Port River shoreline, north-west of Adelaide's CBD.

node.title: High Court narrows NT police officer Zachary Rolfe's use of 'good faith' defence in murder trial
node.description: Northern Territory prosecutors win their High Court appeal challenging Zachary Rolfe's plan to argue he acted in good faith in his role as a police officer as a defence in his murder trial.

node.title: 'Wake-up call' for Gold Coast, Southern Downs after new community COVID cases detected in Queensland
node.description: Two people in the south-east corner have tested positive after potentially being infectious in the community for several days. One case is also detected in hotel quarantine in a person that arrived from Melbourne.

node.title: TGA says 6-year-old who had 'heavy menstrual bleeding' after Pfizer jab was actually aged 41
node.description: Australia's medicines regulator has clarified a mistake on its website that wrongly showed a six-year-old girl had experienced "heavy menstrual bleeding" and other illnesses after receiving the Pfizer vaccine, symptoms which were supposed to be attributed to a 41-year-old woman.

node.title: James Pattinson fined, suspended for dangerous throw
node.description: James Pattinson has been fined his entire match fee for striking Daniel Hughes on the foot with a needless throw during their Sheffield Shield clash at the MCG.

node.title: 'She's nothing like me': Lady Gaga responds to rumours she stayed in character for 18 months for House of Gucci
node.description: Lady Gaga admits she spent nine months in character for her role as Patrizia Reggiani in a film exploring the 1995 murder-for-hire of the heir to Gucci fashion dynasty.
